\n<Marion>I've finally reached the maximum level upgrade possible with
the Grow Cores!

\n<Marion>I've achieved the maximum value for leveling up with the
Grow Cores!
\n<Marion>For now, this is as strong as Eury can get.

\n<Eury>...When you put it that way, it feels kind of sad to hit a
limit.

\n<Marion>Well, you haven't been a modified girl for long, so that's
just how it is.

\n<Eury>By the way, do you think I have a chance of beating Makina-
senpai with my current combat abilities?

\n<Marion>Well, if Makina was completely standing still, maybe you
could win?
\n<Marion>You've got potential, so keep at it.
All Grow Cores have been used.
if(!s[605])メンテナンス（ふりなおし）

Your level will return to 1, and the Grow Cores for the
decreased levels will be extracted. Would you like to
perform maintenance?
\n<Marion>Let's see, if I do this here...

\n<Marion>Voila, maintenance complete. I've extracted all the cores
we've used so far.

\n<Marion>Right now, you're like a Level 1 weakling, so be careful not
to go monster hunting in this state.
\n<Marion>...Why do you ask about that name?

\n<Marion>That's absurd. Ruin was creating something called a
Manoloid?

\n<Marion>To begin with, that guy went completely off the grid after I
completed the modified girl.
\n<Marion>So, I had assumed he died from the monster damage...
\n<Marion>Now, let me read that letter of yours.
We were good friends, both aspiring to be engineers.

But, it was always only you who got recognized for your
achievements.

All of my discoveries were condemned as dangerous and
discarded.

While I couldn't succeed in anything, you somehow completed
the modified girl who would save the world.
I still remember that moment to this day.

Crushed by a sense of inferiority, I thought I never wanted
to see you again.

Even after the modified girl was defeated once and the world
was dominated by monsters, I continued to live in hiding.
...A few months after the original monster was defeated,

I met someone for the first time who acknowledged my
technology.
I followed him and continued to create Manoloids.

My Manoloids will one day defeat the modified girl you
created.
With that sole purpose, I became an ally to the monsters.
Seeing me as I am now, what do you think?
\n<Marion>...So, Eury defeated that Manoloid thing, huh.

\n<Marion>But that alone wouldn't be a reason not to turn into a
monster...
\n<Eury>He said he was in Tengen Street...
\n<Marion>Sorry, but I can't go there. Find him and bring him here!

\n<Marion>Creating monsters is an act too grave to be dismissed as
mere terrorism. He needs to snap out of it quickly...!

\n<Makina>By the way, there's a forest near Tengatsu City. It seems
there was a \C[24]large monster reaction\C[0] there.

\n<Makina>Can you \C[24]patrol\C[0] during the daytime? If there are
any suspicious traces, we'll need to go defeat it at night.

\n<Makina>Take this with you, you can't fight if you run out of
bullets.

the situation is urgent.

\n<Makina>Sorry, but I must go now. Eury, be sure to tackle your
mission without any negligence.

\n<Makina>...If you lose to the monster, who knows what will happen.
Eury, really, don't push yourself too hard.

\n<Marion>During the standby period, it doesn't matter where you are.

\n<Marion>Seriously... Well, I do acknowledge that you defeated

\n<Makina>You're going to your previous business trip location for a
